reviews.text:
👌🏻 Variety of dish/cuisine to choose from. Responsive staff. 

Would be better if it plays RTHK/Viu TV but TVB on the television.
A bit pricey but nice food and staff.

Had a gathering dinner with a group of 7 tonight here. This is our first time trying this hotpot place. I booked a table at 7:30pm tonight and there was no waiting time. The ambient is spacious i think. The restaurant is located on 23/f of a commercial building, so u can even get a clear view of Mong Kok if u sit close by the window. 
 
Their signature dish here is “chicken pot” 雞煲. It is basically a pot of chicken. U can choose whole or half chicken. There are also different favor and cook style to choose from. Also spicy and non-spicy. The price looks a little but on an expensive side however the quality of food is good and justify for the price. Deep fried beancurd (響玲) the one that look like spring roll, is really good. It was freshly made by the restaurant upon order. 

Other ingredients are fresh and good. We also ordered some drinks and beer. We paid $388 per person tonight but we really ordered too much food. I think around $300 would be more comfortable :)
nice place for friend gathering. Price little bit high

Great view at 23/F with the full length windows! Clean and comfortable setting with excellent air conditioning and ventilation. One often gets the smell of cooking in a hot pot joint but it's not the case in this establishment. 

Meatballs, fishballs, squidballs and fish paste were fresh and home made. Soup base is decent but is perhaps a bit too salty. A few of the house specials also look interesting. 

Condiments was generous. Service is friendly and attentive.

Suggest to come early and enjoy the early bird discount (by returning the table and settling the bill by 7:30pm). Otherwise pricing is on the higher side but its worth it.

Happy to come back again and would recommend it for friend or family gathering.
